## Resource Naming Convention

Resources are advertised as Kubernetes extended resources:

- Format: `<vendor-domain>/<resource-type>`
- This project uses `tenstorrent.com` as the vendor domain.
- The resource type should match the card type discovered at runtime
  (e.g. `n150`, `n300`).
- The full resource name (e.g. `tenstorrent.com/n150`) is what users specify
  in pod specs under `resources.limits`.

Example pod spec requesting one device:

```yaml
resources:
  limits:
    tenstorrent.com/n150: 1
```

Extended resources:
- Are always integers (no fractional requests).
- Cannot be overcommitted (limits must equal requests).
- Cannot be shared between containers.

