## AllocateResponse Structure

Each `ContainerAllocateResponse` can specify the following to configure
how the container accesses the device:

```go
type ContainerAllocateResponse struct {
    Envs        map[string]string   // Environment variables
    Mounts      []*Mount            // Bind mounts from host to container
    Devices     []*DeviceSpec       // Device nodes to expose
    Annotations map[string]string   // Container annotations
}

type DeviceSpec struct {
    ContainerPath string  // Path inside the container (e.g. /dev/tenstorrent)
    HostPath      string  // Path on the host (e.g. /dev/tenstorrent)
    Permissions   string  // "r", "w", "m", or combinations like "rw"
}

type Mount struct {
    ContainerPath string  // Mount point inside the container
    HostPath      string  // Path on the host
    ReadOnly      bool
}
```

